n-item__stack-item\"><ul class=\"nova-legacy-e-list nova-legacy-e-list--size-m nova-legacy-e-list--type-inline nova-legacy-e-list--spacing-none nova-legacy-v-publication-item__person-list\"><li class=\"nova-legacy-e-list__item\"><a class=\"nova-legacy-e-link nova-legacy-e-link--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-link--theme-bare\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/scientific-contributions/Deborah-J-Mayhew-2184513990\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-v-person-inline-item\"><span class=\"nova-legacy-v-person-inline-item__fullname\">Deborah J. Mayhew</span></span></a></li></ul></div><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__stack-item\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-e-text nova-legacy-e-text--size-m nova-legacy-e-text--family-sans-serif nova-legacy-e-text--spacing-none nova-legacy-e-text--color-inherit nova-legacy-e-text--clamp-3 nova-legacy-v-publication-item__description\"><span class=\"js-target-abstract-61a68d3838763 lite-page-hidden\">The purpose of this tutorial is to provide a lifecycle of practical usability tasks and techniques for structuring the process of designing good user interfaces to either traditional software applications or Web pages and applets. The tutorial presents techniques which can be applied at different points in a typical product development lifecycle. Techniques presented include not only requirements analysis, design and testing techniques, but also organizational and managerial strategies.</span></div></div></div></div><footer class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__footer\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-v-publication-item__footer-actions\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-pack nova-legacy-o-pack--gutter-m nova-legacy-o-pack--width-auto nova-legacy-o-pack--vertical-align-middle\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-o-pack__item nova-legacy-v-publication-item__footer-button-group\"><div class=\"nova-legacy-c-button-group nova-legacy-c-button-group--gutter-m nova-legacy-c-button-group--orientation-horizontal nova-legacy-c-button-group--width-auto nova-legacy-v-publication-